  "question_id": "8b895357-6fb9-4e84-a194-0ec53677dcec",
  "short_text": "First N Natural Numbers (For Loop)",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a number `N` and prints Natural Numbers from **1** to `N`.\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n* All the positive numbers from **1** are called **Natural Numbers**.\n* Use the **For** loop to iterate over the range of numbers.\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should contain all the Natural Numbers from **1** to `N`, each on a new line.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 7`,\n\n- The Natural Numbers from **1** to **7** are **1**, **2**, **3**, **4**, **5**, **6** and **7**.\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n6\n7\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "91a75433-8294-42bd-aa5e-bdd76c661a6d",
      "code_content": "number = int(input())\n\nfor each_num in range(1, number + 1):\n    print(each_num)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
